{
  "texts": [
    "However, once a student interacts with an externally hosted chatbot, that interaction is lost to the instructional team.",
    "Indeed, it has been argued that interactions with our students are one of the ways in which learning can be made more effective [5].",
    "By developing a locally hosted chatbot, opportunities for logging rich interaction data are available.",
    "Access to these logs can provide key insights into what students are struggling with, the relative importance they put onto certain topics, and even give a snapshot into how and when they are studying.",
    "Furthermore, access to hosted chatbots using students' personal accounts creates a divide between students with the resources to afford access and students who cannot, or will not, purchase that access."
  ]
}